\cf0 We developed a fully automated method for measuring the radial fluorescence intensity profile of antibodies labelling proteins on the apical surface of hair cells. The method relies on detecting the apical surface centroids of hair cells from stainings of a cytoskeletal marker that labels the cuticular plates (i. e. actin or spectrin) using the MaximumFinder plugin [ref], where the noise tolerance threshold was adjusted to achieve detection of the correct range of cell numbers per neuromasts. The normalized fluorescence intensity of the protein of interest (i. e. Vangl2 or Gnai) is then measured within a specified radial interval around the centroid for varying angles.\
